<title>USA: Cascade to acquire co for 3.8 mln shrs.</title>
<headline>Cascade to acquire co for 3.8 mln shrs.</headline>
<dateline>WESTFORD, Mass. 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Cascade Communications Corp on Thursday said it agreed to acquire Sahara Networks Inc in a stock transaction valued at about $212.8 million.</p>
<p>Under the deal, Cascade will acquire the private Sarhara, a developer of broadband access products, in exchange for 3.8 million shares of Cascade common stock.</p>
<p>The deal is expected to be completed this month.</p>
<p>Cascade said the transaction will be accounted for as a purchase of in-process research and development with a one-time write-off. The company did not specify the size of the write-off.</p>
